The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for intrusion detection in multi-cloud environments, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on the use of supervised machine learning techniques for anomaly detection and categorization, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the need for better network infrastructure and load balancing, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for appropriate countermeasures and defense against attacks, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE).
